<figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Greatest_common_divisor.png" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Greatest_common_divisor.png/250px-Greatest_common_divisor.png" decoding="async" width="250" height="128" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1f/Greatest_common_divisor.png/500px-Greatest_common_divisor.png 2x" data-file-width="1225" data-file-height="628" /></a><figcaption><a href="/wiki/Thomae%27s_function" title="Thomae&#39;s function">Thomae's function</a></figcaption></figure>
<p>If <span class="texhtml"><i>a</i></span> and <span class="texhtml"><i>b</i></span> are both nonzero, the greatest common divisor of <span class="texhtml"><i>a</i></span> and <span class="texhtml"><i>b</i></span> can be computed by using <a href="/wiki/Least_common_multiple" title="Least common multiple">least common multiple</a> (LCM) of <span class="texhtml"><i>a</i></span> and&#160;<span class="texhtml"><i>b</i></span>:
</p>
